The sequences have been deposited under accession numbers KU646847- KU646856. The nucleotide sequences of partial N and L genes of the five Malaysian isolates and the outgroup sequences were aligned using Mega 7.0 software. Based on the phylogenetic tree of partial L (Fig. 2
) and N genes (Fig. 3
), all Malaysian isolates (UPM23; PCS139; UPM10; UPM53; RSS88) were clustered together and were closely related to the isolates reported from Hong Kong (M252A); Thailand (Thai-U16) and Japan (SS3, MiJP003,ChJP073, N153U, N040 K, N028 K, N141U, N010U). All previously reported FeMV formed a distinct cluster in the phylogenetic tree which was separated from the other members of the genus Morbillivirus.
